<Author>amalia24
<Content>would stay there agian Hotel exceeded my expectations. The rooms were very clean comfortable. Kitchens in the suits were well equipped and staff service was great. Had booked a two bedroom unit and was upgraded to a three on arrival!! Loved how there were two bathrooms and the balcony was nice for drying bathing suits. I have stayed at a number of places in Puerto Rico and this hotel gives you the most bang for your buck. I would highly recommend this hotel to singles and families alike! Should mention the hotel is not geared for people looking to spend a lot of time there,. The pool is nothing to get excited over and there is not a real common area to be in. 
